<br>
1. Market Square seems to be in direct opposition to Verants intended cultural barriers. It is in effect an exploit to get around such barriers. One may argue that any message board is an exploit to get around the language barrier. While this is true, non merchandise boards do not have a significant effect on the server.<br>
<br>
2. Merchant boards have a direct and huge influence on server economy. In general, they maintain a sellers market. The seller can afford to be patient while his post gets hits until his price is met. In-game only merchanting demands that the sellers time must be invested in order to move his merchandise. This greatly reduces a sellers advantage, and places the economics of the server in-game rather than on the WWW.<br>
<br>
3. It's not supposed to be easy.<br>
<br>
I trust that Market Square is well intended, but still I have to protest it's existence. FV will decay eventually and irregardless of our protections in this and other matters. I think we need to delay that inevitable demise as much as we can by preserving the integrity of the server everywhere we can. <br>
<br>
Zarsiss Razorscale<br>
